WRITTEN BY: MATTHEW TROTTER
THIS UTILITY SHOULD BE INSTALLED BY MOVING THE FOLLOWING SCRIPT INTO THE LOCAL BIN FOLDER
/usr/local/bin/count

USE UTILITY EXMAPLE:
If you wish to count humber of items in your current working directory simply type count for example:
rootprmpt#> count

If you wish to count number of files in another directory simeply type count and name of folder or path of directory for exmaple:
rootprompt#> count </path/of/directory>

UTILIY WILL IMMEDIATELY COUNT ALL ITEMS INSIDE OF A FOLDER AND RETURN THE NUMBER


